                  Nordic Investment Bank                

 | Helsinki, Finland                

An international financial institution owned by eight member countries: Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Iceland, Latvia, Lithuania, Norway, and Sweden.

 
 

 

"We depend on Information Builders technology to provide insights to finance, accounting, risk management, treasury, lending, and other parts of the organization."
Aini Joensuu
	Chief Systems Officer

 
 




            Nordic Investment Bank Thrives in Volatile Financial Markets With Analytics 
          













                    The Challenge        





To thrive in the volatile financial market, and comply with its many regulations, NIB chose to turn to business intelligence (BI) and analytics.







                    The Solution        





WebFOCUS has enabled the development of an analytics portal that includes dashboards, InfoApps™, and reports for lending, accounting, treasury, administration, planning, and risk management.







                    The Success        





Employees are most satisfied with the flexibility of WebFOCUS, which enables users to slice and dice relevant information via charts, graphs, reports, data visualizations, and other interactive methods, at any time on demand.







                    The Products        





WebFOCUS, DataMigrator, and adapters for Sybase, SQL Server, SAP, and Excel.






 







                    More About Nordic Investment Bank                  




