          Nordic Investment Bank Uses Analytics to Thrive in Volatile Financial Markets        


























 


WebFOCUS BI Platform Gives International Lender a Competitive Edge
Rapid changes are occurring in the financial services industry, even as the expected time to market for new lending products and services has decreased. Banks and lenders need rigorous information management practices to survive and first-rate analytics technology to thrive. They also need to comply with strict regulations governing credit ratings, loan approval standards, and liquidity requirements. Meeting these requirements has become increasingly difficult in the wake of new government regulations, from Basel III guidelines to Money Market Fund Reform rules, which happened after the global financial meltdown. Nordic Investment Bank (NIB) has standardized on Information Builders' WebFOCUS business intelligence (BI) and analytics platform to meet these business challenges head on.
Headquartered in Helsinki, Finland, NIB is an international financial institution jointly owned by Denmark, Finland, Iceland, Norway, Sweden, Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania. NIB borrows funds on the international capital markets and offers long-term lending to private and public entities to complement commercial lending. Its bonds enjoy the highest possible credit rating.
"We depend on Information Builders' technology and local InfoBuild services to provide insights to lending, finance, accounting, risk management, treasury, and other parts of the organization," says Aini Joensuu, chief systems officer at NIB. "WebFOCUS is essential for information management and compliance."
WebFOCUS for Interactive Reporting
Joensuu and her team implemented a portal with dashboards for accounting, treasury, administration, planning, and risk management. The portal lets authorized users access current information on demand. Users easily explore data via reports, graphs, and charts. These analytics assets leverage many core WebFOCUS features, such as WebFOCUS ReportCaster, to send information directly to people’s e-mails. "We depend on WebFOCUS parameterization and Active Technologies across all our departments," Joensuu notes. "Nearly everybody in the organization can access WebFOCUS. We have more than 250 users."
Information Builders calls interactive analytics applications InfoApps™ since they allow people to visualize data in charts and graphs and easily drill into the data. Users can find and compare relevant data elements, and then select an output format to save, display, or analyze the data, including HTML, Excel, and PDF.
"WebFOCUS puts our data in a very accessible form," says Jaana Ijas, a senior system specialist at NIB who spearheads much of the WebFOCUS development. "If users want to examine lending data in a particular sector, they start with a portfolio at the summary level, and drill down to the detail level as they examine the information."
Addressing Regulatory Compliance
All banks face tough lending standards and conservative guidelines for capital reserves. As an international finance institution, NIB ensures that it complies with regulations. NIB also tracks its lending activity by business areas, such as energy and environment; infrastructure, transportation, and telecom; industries and services; and financial institutions and small and medium-size enterprises (SMEs). Officers in the Treasury and Risk departments use WebFOCUS to analyze liquidity as they monitor the inflow and outflow of funds by sector, time period, portfolio, and other variables. An InfoApp™ computes liquidity buffer survival horizons – projections of financial liquidity based on current and expected lending activity.
"As our lending system establishes payment plans, funding officers need to compare what actually comes in with what is expected to come in," Ijas explains. "What are the expected distributions against the expected amounts of these loans over a particular time period?"
This same logic applies to treasury instruments. WebFOCUS lets treasury officers calculate risk patterns for inflows and outflows among any group of customers, ensuring that NIB maintains adequate survival horizons. Other WebFOCUS reports enable the accounting department to reconcile balances and verify that transactions have been correctly posted from sub-ledgers to the general ledger. "Cash flow and compliance are dependent on the ability to access and analyze this information," Ijas adds.
DataMigrator Prepares the Data
WebFOCUS acquires data from a Microsoft SQL Server data warehouse, which is periodically loaded with operational information from an SAP enterprise resource planning (ERP) system, a customized lending system, a treasury system, and other operational databases, including text files and CSV files. Every day, iWay DataMigrator, also from Information Builders, grabs relevant information from these source systems and loads it into the warehouse, merging relational data with flat-file data and putting it all into a common format, behind the scenes. DataMigrator handles all necessary conversions and transpositions to ensure consistent financial and operational reporting.
WebFOCUS pre-aggregates the data into a reporting warehouse to ensure that users obtain results quickly. Users in each department and corporate domain are authorized to see only certain portions of the database, based on their specific needs and the controls built into the security profile. WebFOCUS also accesses data directly from the source systems. Having a combination of real-time and staged data sources gives NIB personnel flexibility to satisfy reporting and analytics needs. ReportCaster automatically generates standard reports and places them in the reporting library for auditing purposes. ReportCaster also sends reports to e-mail addresses and printers, and distributes files for other processes, but mainly reports are run on demand.
"We can access various kinds of data and combine it as we need it," Joensuu confirms. "WebFOCUS has been a huge timesaver."
For example, risk officers must submit information to oversight boards three times per year to verify liquidity recovery ratios. Previously, they had to manually pull information from several different information systems and load it into Excel tables to calculate these ratios, which was cumbersome and time-consuming. "Now people use WebFOCUS reports for this, ensuring accuracy and saving many hours of work," Joensuu says. "They can see the data any time rather than merely at these periodic intervals. WebFOCUS not only makes it easy to get the data we need, but also improves this business process."
Evolving With the Data
Emerging market trends, shifting industry regulations, and new competitive forces necessitate new types of reporting, analysis, and information management. In response, NIB has developed a more robust enterprise data warehouse. It plans to use DataMigrator to load the warehouse and WebFOCUS to add new types of reports, dashboards, and InfoApps™ to the portal – as well as to explore Information Builders' master data management (MDM) technology to automate data enrichment and data quality initiatives.
"We work with InfoBuild on an ongoing basis, and we are satisfied with their ability to implement Information Builders’ technology," Joensuu concludes. "Their consultants have a good handle on our needs and Information Builders continues to supply advanced technology for our needs."

 






 







        The Organization:
      
An international financial institution owned by eight member countries: Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Iceland, Latvia, Lithuania, Norway and Sweden.



        The Challenge:
      
To comply with international accounting standards and lending guidelines, NIB continually monitors lending activity, liquidity, and cash flow by business sector, region, timeframe, and other variables.



        The Strategy:
      
Develop an analytic portal that includes dashboards, InfoApps, and reports for lending, accounting, treasury, administration, planning, and risk management. Enable users to slice and dice relevant information at any time on demand.



        The Results:
      
Employees are most satisfied with the flexibility of WebFOCUS, which empowers the users to easily explore data via charts, graphs, reports, data visualizations, and other interactive methods – with information always presented uniformly.



        Information Builders Solution:
      
WebFOCUS, DataMigrator, and adapters for Sybase, SQL Server, SAP, and Excel.



